reviewText: "Australia's Answer to "Family Guy" But Wronger!"That was the tag-line that Amazon had put on this movie.  As several others have mentioned it is not even remotely the same kind of humor as family guy, it is indeed (as one may guess) nothing but a poorly strung together set of little johnny jokes.  The humor falls flat seeming to depend highly on the concept that swearing is funny.  Because almost all of the jokes the punchline is Johnny swearing.  The thing about little Johnny jokes is they are burn out pretty easily, the more you hear them the less funny they are.  On top of that most of these are jokes you have heard over and over again.  It fizzles and dies pretty quickly.A more appropriate tag line would be: "Old rehashed jokes, nothing at all like "Family Guy", and much worse"
summary: Sad string of jokes where swearing is the punchline, maybe funny if you are under 10.
Title: Little Johnny the Movie

reviewText: I struggled through the first 20 minutes before giving up. The animation was just fair and the jokes were stale and the movie really dragged on. Very slow, plodding animation. There were no real laughs. Meh!
summary: not at all similar to family guy!
Title: Little Johnny the Movie

reviewText: Pretty enjoyable animated movie from down under. Advertises as Family Guy like but wronger. Not really so though. But pretty good
Title: Little Johnny the Movie

reviewText: It is simply a fun watching an animation of school kids mimicking the adults while smart ass Johnny commented the events well reflecting a brutal meaningless surrounding existence in picturesque Australia changed not much since an original B&W; 1967 year anime version.Today, probably, such a kid ought to be referred to a psychologist with all the records following him upon a life spin and parents could a little to do.
Title: Little Johnny the Movie

reviewText: It's so rare that I give a movie a one star review, but this was easily one of the worst movies I have ever seen... little needs to be said about it except that basically every one of the jokes is recycled from old Little Johnny jokes, so if you've heard them, you've seen the movie, the animation is awful, looks as if it was made in the '70s, and the plot is barely there.I try not to be a cynic, but when you watch a movie without a fraction of originality, it's hard not to be.  Even the attempts at being "offensively funny" with the minorities portrayed fall so flat on their face that you can't even feel offended.If you have never heard a joke in your life, then this may give you a laugh or two... other than that, this movie is impossible to recommend on any level.
Title: Little Johnny the Movie
